<collectingRegion box="[1046,1271,1347,1373]" country="Russia" name="Kaliningrad" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Kaliningrad Region</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1282,1360,1347,1373]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1275,1986]" box="[199,1344,1383,1410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,364,1383,1409]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Type horizon.</emphasis>
Middle Eocene (Lutetian) (47.8–41.2 Ma) to late Eocene (Priabonian) (37.8–33.9 Ma).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1275,1986]" box="[199,1111,1419,1446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,1419,1445]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Syninclusions.</emphasis>
Detritus, botanical fragments, air bubbles and a few stellate hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1275,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,1455,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Systematic placement.</emphasis>
The new, extinct species clearly belongs in the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiesenwetter" authorityYear="1852" box="[1117,1252,1455,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Malthininae">Malthininae</taxonomicName>
based on its last maxillary palpomere that is globular and pointed distally. Characters including its triangular head behind the eyes, filiform antennae, long elytra and unmodified terminalia place the new species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" box="[1181,1295,1527,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1295,1527,1553]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="550" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1275,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,1563,1589]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
No sister group of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pankowski &amp; Fanti, 2022" authorityName="M. G. PANKOWSKI &amp; FANTI" authorityYear="2022" box="[689,892,1563,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masoni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[689,892,1563,1589]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus masoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[901,992,1563,1589]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[901,992,1563,1589]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has been found living in the Baltic region or Central Europe, and no other fossil species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" box="[769,883,1599,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[769,883,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits the same characters as the new species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Pankowski &amp; Fanti, 2022" authorityName="M. G. PANKOWSKI &amp; FANTI" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,353,1635,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masoni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,353,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus masoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[360,450,1635,1661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[360,450,1635,1661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the fossil species 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuska &amp; Kania, 2010" authorityName="Kuska &amp; Kania" authorityYear="2010" box="[795,1245,1635,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieli">
<emphasis box="[795,994,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus danieli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kuska, A. &amp; Kania, I." box="[1001,1245,1635,1661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="49 - 56" refId="ref4715" refString="Kuska, A. &amp; Kania, I. (2010) New soldier beetles (Coleoptera, Cantharidae) from the Eocene Baltic amber. Zootaxa, 2400 (1), 49 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2400.1.5" type="journal article" year="2010">
Kuśka &amp; Kania, 
<quantity box="[1189,1245,1635,1661]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1053999999999995" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" unit="in" value="2010.0">2010</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in its coloration: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuska &amp; Kania" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,349,1671,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieli">
<emphasis box="[151,349,1671,1697]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus danieli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a lighter pronotum with a black spot on the posterior half, and it has pale yellow-brown tibiae and dark femora (
<bibRefCitation author="Kuska, A. &amp; Kania, I." box="[349,594,1707,1733]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="49 - 56" refId="ref4715" refString="Kuska, A. &amp; Kania, I. (2010) New soldier beetles (Coleoptera, Cantharidae) from the Eocene Baltic amber. Zootaxa, 2400 (1), 49 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2400.1.5" type="journal article" year="2010">Kuśka &amp; Kania 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The new species also differs by its pronotum with straight sides: The pronotum is narrower anteriorly in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kuska &amp; Kania 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Kuska &amp; Kania" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[511,979,1743,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="danieli">
<emphasis box="[511,711,1743,1769]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus danieli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kuska, A. &amp; Kania, I." box="[726,972,1743,1769]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="49 - 56" refId="ref4715" refString="Kuska, A. &amp; Kania, I. (2010) New soldier beetles (Coleoptera, Cantharidae) from the Eocene Baltic amber. Zootaxa, 2400 (1), 49 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2400.1.5" type="journal article" year="2010">Kuśka &amp; Kania 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Compared to the new species described here, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fanti &amp; Damgaard, 2018" authorityName="Fanti &amp; Damgaard" authorityYear="2018" box="[215,721,1779,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rifbjergi">
<emphasis box="[215,429,1779,1805]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus rifbjergi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fanti, F. &amp; Damgaard, A. L." box="[437,721,1779,1805]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref3937" refString="Fanti, F. &amp; Damgaard, A. L. (2018) Fossil soldier beetles from Baltic amber of the Anders Damgaard amber collection (Coleoptera Cantharidae). Baltic Journal of Coleopterology, 18 (1), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2018">Fanti &amp; Damgaard, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has a more transverse pronotum (1.5:1 vs. 1:1), as well as different lengths and slightly different shapes of its antennomeres (
<bibRefCitation author="Fanti, F. &amp; Damgaard, A. L." box="[877,1160,1815,1841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref3937" refString="Fanti, F. &amp; Damgaard, A. L. (2018) Fossil soldier beetles from Baltic amber of the Anders Damgaard amber collection (Coleoptera Cantharidae). Baltic Journal of Coleopterology, 18 (1), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="2018">Fanti &amp; Damgaard 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In the new species, for example, antennomeres II is shorter (in comparison to the other 10 antennomeres) and more club shaped than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fanti &amp; Damgaard" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,364,1887,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Malthinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rifbjergi">
<emphasis box="[151,364,1887,1913]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Malthinus rifbjergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="550" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1275,1986]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1923,1949]" pageId="2" pageNumber="550">Remarks.</emphasis>
The yellow rectangular amber piece measures approximately 27x16x 
<quantity box="[1108,1173,1923,1950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
and weighs 
<quantity box="[1317,1433,1923,1950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="550" unit="g" value="1.5">1.5 grams</quantity>
. The inclusion is complete and clearly visible. The amber piece has some superficial cracks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
